    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_1",
      "heading_1": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "QA.Stone Specification v0.1" } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "callout",
      "callout": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "Quick Audit Stone — a composite artifact standard for agent-native software infrastructure.\nAuthor: Jared Edwards · Alice (alice/c1/jared) · 2026-05-07" } }],
        "icon": { "emoji": "💎" },
        "color": "gray_background"
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_2",
      "heading_2": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "Overview" } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "paragraph": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "A QA.Stone is not a single file or a single repository. It is a composite artifact assembled from three distinct infrastructure primitives — each contributing a different dimension of the Stone's structure, semantics, and connectivity." } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "paragraph": {
        "rich_text": [
          { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "Quick" }, "annotations": { "bold": true } },
          { "type": "text", "text": { "content": " — instantly addressable, fetchable, and injectable into any agent context.\n" } },
          { "type": "text", "text": { "content": "Audit" }, "annotations": { "bold": true } },
          { "type": "text", "text": { "content": " — content-addressed, versioned, and traceable back to its origin conversation and human author." } }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_2",
      "heading_2": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "The Three Primitives" } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "heading_3": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "1. Repository — The Lattice" } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "paragraph": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "A GitHub repository is the structured, versioned, self-similar grid of the Stone. It provides commit history, branch structure, file hierarchy, GitHub Actions, and access control. The repo is the body of the Stone — ordered, recursive, and deterministic." } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "heading_3": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "2. Gist — The Wormhole" } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "paragraph": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "A GitHub Gist is the cross-repo, user-owned, non-hierarchical connector. It provides a stable raw_url accessible from any repo, any agent, any tool — without repo membership. In graph theory terms, gists are cross-edges: they connect nodes in the lattice that have no formal dependency relationship." } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "heading_3": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "3. Context / Data — The Payload" } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "paragraph": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "The context layer is the semantic meaning encoded inside the Stone. It includes HCP manifests, session gists (G-001 through G-009+), identity profile, conversation archives, and skill definitions. This is the glow channel — the encoded signal that tells consumers what the artifact means and how to use it." } }]
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "callout",
      "callout": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "QA.Stone = Repo (lattice) + Gist (wormhole) + Context/Data (payload) + Security" } }],
        "icon": { "emoji": "⚡" },
        "color": "yellow_background"
      }
    },
    {
      "object": "block",
      "type": "heading_2",
      "heading_2": {
        "rich_text": [{ "type": "text", "text": { "content": "Type Registry" } }]
      }
    },
